                            <comment id="69270" author="niu" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2013 03:44:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;logs: &lt;a href=&quot;ftp://ftp.whamcloud.com/uploads/LU-4110&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;ftp://ftp.whamcloud.com/uploads/LU-4110&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I didn&apos;t find anything abnormal in the logs, and the test passed successfully. Maybe there was some connection problem between OST-0001b with MDT?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please keep reporting if you find anything wrong. Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="69111" author="niu" created="Wed, 16 Oct 2013 13:35:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could you collect log (with D_QUOTA enabled) for OST-0001b and MDT? Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Enable D_QUOTA by &quot;echo +quota &amp;gt; /proc/sys/lnet/debug&quot; on OSS (which OST-0001b located) and MDS;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lctl debug_daemon start tmpfile 500; (on OSS &amp;amp; MDS)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lctl mark &quot;=== start test&quot;; (on OSS &amp;amp; MDS)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Write to the file which is striped on OST-0001b as user eric; (on client)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lctl debug_daemon stop; (on OSS &amp;amp; MDS)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lctl debug_file tmpfile logfile; (on OSS &amp;amp; MDS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Hope we can find something useful from the logfiles.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
